FROM THE GATEWAYS TO MEXICO
From NEW YORK-First and Tourist Class...daily
non-stop jet-prop Britannia flights to Mexico City
...DC-6 connections to Acapulco.
From TIJUANA (San Diego)— First Class DC-6
flights...daily non-stop to Guadalajara, one stop to
Mexico City...three weekly flights to La Paz and
Mazatlan...(4 DC-6 flights daily to Acapulco.)
From CD. JUAREZ (El Paso)-First Class DC-6
daily to Chihuahua, Torreon, Mexico City...con-
necting flights to Acapulco.
From NOGALES—DC-3 service (3 days a week)
to Mexico City and Chihuahua and all Pacific
Mexican Coastal Cities.
From SAN ANTONIO-First Class DC-6 flights...
daily (ex. Mon.) to Monterrey, Torreon,
Mazatlan,
Guadalajara and Acapulco.
From TUCSON-First Class DC-6 flights...daily
to Mexico City...connecting
flights to Acapulco
and all Pacific Coastal Cities.
ACAPULCO
FINEST OF EQUIPMENT
Aeronaves
equipment includes Bristol Britannia
Turbo Prop-Jets, and radar-equipped Douglas DC-6
Airliners, and are flown by experienced and trained
pilots and carefully maintained by skilled trained
mechanics.
CONTINENTAL SERVICE
Luxurious, spacious seating...continental cuisine
and traditional Mexican cocktail hour* …courteous
stewardess and steward service in the gracious
tradition of Mexican hospitality.
27 YEARS OF SERVICE TO MAJOR MEXICAN CITIES
Aeronaves de Mexico domestic service covers 34
cities and 78,000 miles per day, and offers con-
venient connections to Central and South America.
Aeronaves is the only airline serving Acapulco.
* except Tourist N.Y.
AERONAVES
DE
